X_Steem Note is a desktop offline application that allows you to write to, save and open files of different formats such as txt, rtf, doc, html and many other formats. 
Unlike most notepad apps currently in the market,
X_Steem Note has been designed to be colorful and beautiful.

### Installation Requirements

Windows	OS 7, 8, 10.

* Java Runtime Environment:	http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/jre8-downloads-2133155.html
* GEt source, Clone the git Repository: https://github.com/neduzze5/X_Steem-Note
* Download the jar file: https://github.com/neduzze5/X_Steem-Note/blob/master/dist/X-Steem_Note.jar

Simply run the jar file and begin typing and saving in your notes.

### How to use the application

* Open the X-Steem-Notes application
Click on the **New Note** Button or the **Begin icon** at the middle of the application
![5a](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35721447/38874483-1640f8ac-4250-11e8-8f9a-ddbbfd79a261.png)

* Type in the notes you want to save, or paste using the shortcut **Ctrl+V** or click the Edit Icon at the top and select paste, once done you can save your note by clicking on the save icon below the page of the application.
![5b](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35721447/38874871-0dbbc274-4251-11e8-9243-e20e52446730.png)
Then you can input the title for your new note and select a directory on your PC to save.

![5d](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35721447/38875430-42798ea0-4252-11e8-887c-7dd901837c1a.png)


* The file button at the top gives you access to begin a new note or load your previously saved noted.
![5c](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35721447/38875306-fbf77ff0-4251-11e8-96b2-15a801892b5d.png)

* The Edit Button can be used for three actions , **Copy**, **Cut** and **Paste**.
